if you get hurt.

468
00:33:05,095 --> 00:33:07,015
-Alrighty.
-We got a deal.

469
00:33:07,455 --> 00:33:09,295
No, not quite.

470
00:33:09,455 --> 00:33:11,335
I'm gonna teach you how to fight...

471
00:33:11,495 --> 00:33:14,095
...then we'll get you a manager,
and I'm off down the road.

472
00:33:14,255 --> 00:33:17,695
-I hate to argue with you, but--
-Don't argue, that's the way we're doing it.

473
00:33:17,855 --> 00:33:21,455
I teach you all you need to know,
and you go off and make a million dollars.

474
00:33:21,655 --> 00:33:24,455
I don't care. You get your teeth
knocked out, I don't care.

475
00:33:24,615 --> 00:33:27,695
I don't wanna hear about it.
That's just the way it's gonna be.

476
00:33:27,855 --> 00:33:29,335
It's the only way I'll do it.

477
00:33:37,255 --> 00:33:38,375
All right.

478
00:33:39,455 --> 00:33:44,215
Now, one of the things I've noticed around
the gym is you never move your feet.

479
00:33:44,375 --> 00:33:47,535
You stand there just flat-footed.
You've gotta move your feet.

480
00:33:47,735 --> 00:33:49,775
That's one of the best things
I can teach you.

481
00:33:49,975 --> 00:33:52,655
So here's what you do.

482
00:33:52,895 --> 00:33:55,215
You get yourself--
Bend your knees a little bit.

483
00:33:55,695 --> 00:33:59,095
Get in an athletic position.
Look like you're gonna hit something.

484
00:34:01,335 --> 00:34:04,135
-Move them how, boss?
-Just-- Go-- Hit the bag.

485
00:34:05,935 --> 00:34:07,655
-Stop.
-What'd I do wrong?

486
00:34:07,815 --> 00:34:09,895
Okay, you did two things wrong.

487
00:34:10,055 --> 00:34:13,255
One is you asked a question,
and two is you asked another question.

488
00:34:13,735 --> 00:34:17,415
Now, what I want you to do,
it's not about hitting it hard...

489
00:34:17,575 --> 00:34:21,335
...it's how good you hit it. So watch me.

490
00:34:21,495 --> 00:34:23,055
You can count with me if you want.

491
00:34:23,255 --> 00:34:25,935
It's just count. On a one-count,
I hit right through the bag.

492
00:34:26,135 --> 00:34:28,015
-Can you show me that again?
-I just--

493
00:34:28,215 --> 00:34:30,135
Just say "one," please.

494
00:34:30,295 --> 00:34:31,735
-One.
-Okay.

495
00:34:31,895 --> 00:34:33,655
-One. Okay.
-One.

496
00:34:33,815 --> 00:34:36,815
Yeah, just say "one." That's good.
That's good.

497
00:34:37,015 --> 00:34:41,455
Then I move over to my right foot. You'll
see my weight is shifting to my right foot.

498
00:34:41,895 --> 00:34:46,615
Then I hit it with my back of my hand, sort
of like I'm chipping ice with an ice pick.

499
00:34:46,775 --> 00:34:51,935
Then I come over, and I shift to my left foot,
and I hit it with my right hand.

500
00:34:52,095 --> 00:34:54,575
And ice pick maneuver again.

501
00:34:54,735 --> 00:34:57,655
And I come over on my right foot
and hit it right.

502
00:34:59,175 --> 00:35:01,775
Don't watch anything but my feet.

503
00:35:12,775 --> 00:35:16,135
Just do it like that. Just keep practicing.

504
00:35:45,015 --> 00:35:48,655
<i>You show them how to stand,
keep their legs under their shoulders.</i>

505
00:35:56,735 --> 00:36:00,255
<i>To make a fighter,
you gotta strip them down to bare wood.</i>

506
00:36:00,415 --> 00:36:01,855
Rest when you're dead.

507
00:36:02,015 --> 00:36:03,615
Come here.

508
00:36:07,935 --> 00:36:10,495
<i>You can't just tell them
to forget everything you know...</i>

509
00:36:10,655 --> 00:36:13,575
<i>...you gotta make them forget it
in their bones.</i>

510
00:36:17,455 --> 00:36:19,695
<i>Make them so tired
they only listen to you.</i>

511
00:36:19,855 --> 00:36:23,735
<i>Only hear your voice,
only do what you say, and nothing else.</i>

512
00:36:23,895 --> 00:36:25,095
Move your feet.

513
00:36:25,255 --> 00:36:27,175
Move your feet around. Let's see you go.

514
00:36:41,335 --> 00:36:44,655
<i>Show them how to keep their balance
and take it away from the other guy.</i>

515
00:36:44,855 --> 00:36:48,415
Not so low. Look at me.
Right hook and just turn right.

516
00:36:52,615 --> 00:36:55,215
<i>How to generate momentum
off your right toe.</i>

517
00:36:56,855 --> 00:36:59,535
<i>And how to flex your knees
when you fire a jab.</i>

518
00:37:05,575 --> 00:37:09,655
<i>How to fight backing up, so that the
other guy doesn't wanna come after you.</i>

519
00:37:10,215 --> 00:37:12,335
<i>Then you gotta show them
all over again.</i>

520
00:37:12,535 --> 00:37:14,615
<i>Over and over and over...</i>

521
00:37:14,775 --> 00:37:17,655
<i>...till they think they were born that way.</i>

522
00:37:19,335 --> 00:37:20,535
Shift.

523
00:37:20,695 --> 00:37:22,535
Shift away.

524
00:37:23,535 --> 00:37:26,575
Okay. That's enough for today.

525
00:37:26,735 --> 00:37:30,015
Good work. Good girl.

526
00:37:31,255 --> 00:37:33,815
You think I ready for a fight, boss?

527
00:37:55,415 --> 00:37:58,735
Hey. Hey, come here.

528
00:38:01,415 --> 00:38:02,575
You're not breathing.

529
00:38:04,175 --> 00:38:05,815
Hate to disagree with you.

530
00:38:06,415 --> 00:38:09,135
Every time you get under pressure,
you're holding your breath.

531
00:38:09,295 --> 00:38:12,575
-Now, stop doing that.
-Okay.

532
00:38:12,735 --> 00:38:14,935
But other than that,
I'm doing pretty good, right?

533
00:38:15,455 --> 00:38:18,855
-I mean, for a girl.
-I don't train girls.

534
00:38:21,535 --> 00:38:23,615
Think I might be ready
for a fight, boss?

535
00:38:23,775 --> 00:38:27,175
Well, we'll get a manager,
and we'll find out, won't we?

536
00:38:27,335 --> 00:38:30,215
I'd like to,
but you been keeping me too busy.

537
00:38:36,815 --> 00:38:39,495
-Got any family, boss?
-What?

538
00:38:41,975 --> 00:38:45,175
You been spending all this time with me,
I didn't know if you had any.

539
00:38:46,135 --> 00:38:47,335
No.

540
00:38:48,975 --> 00:38:51,215
Well, I've got a daughter, Katy.

541
00:38:51,975 --> 00:38:53,135
That's family.

542
00:38:53,895 --> 00:38:55,895
We're not exactly close.

543
00:38:56,335 --> 00:38:57,735
How much she weigh?

544
00:38:58,935 --> 00:39:00,175
What?

545
00:39:00,375 --> 00:39:03,415
Trouble in my family
comes by the pound.

546
00:39:05,655 --> 00:39:07,215
Yeah.

547
00:39:07,495 --> 00:39:09,495
Not very big.

548
00:39:09,775 --> 00:39:13,575
Used to be real athletic.
Don't know if she kept it up.

549
00:39:19,415 --> 00:39:22,775
So, what do you think?

550
00:39:22,935 --> 00:39:24,775
I ready for a fight?

551
00:39:30,295 --> 00:39:32,015
Hey, Sally.

552
00:39:33,575 --> 00:39:35,015
Come here for a minute, will you?

553
00:39:36,855 --> 00:39:39,535
Frankie, I need to see you
in the back for a minute, okay?

554
00:39:40,175 --> 00:39:43,375
-Can I see you a minute?
-Sally here's a real good manager.

555
00:39:43,575 --> 00:39:47,335
Has a couple of Golden Glove boys.
Looking for a girl, Sally?

556
00:39:47,535 --> 00:39:49,415
I'm looking for a good one.

557
00:39:49,815 --> 00:39:52,615
Well, see, there you go.

558
00:39:55,255 --> 00:39:56,975
Nice working with you, girlie.

559
00:40:00,775 --> 00:40:02,935
-What'd you want?
-Nothing. It's nothing.

560
00:40:03,095 --> 00:40:07,055
I ain't lying, I've been watching you work.
You got a hell of a left.

561
00:40:07,455 --> 00:40:08,775
Thank you.

562
00:40:10,615 --> 00:40:14,135
So you wanna give this a try?
See if it's a fit?

563
00:40:16,215 --> 00:40:19,255
-Yeah, sure.
-Good.

564
00:40:19,415 --> 00:40:21,815
Because I think you're ready for a fight.

565
00:40:33,535 --> 00:40:34,975
Break.

566
00:40:36,215 --> 00:40:39,175
What am I doing wrong, Sally?
Every time I get inside, she's on me.

567
00:40:39,335 --> 00:40:41,935
You're doing great.
You're wearing her down. Keep punching.

568
00:40:42,095 --> 00:40:45,255
-I ain't doing great, I'm losing.
-You're wearing her down.

569
00:40:46,855 --> 00:40:48,615
You okay, honey? Can you see okay?

570
00:40:50,055 --> 00:40:52,055
-Come on.
-Do it.

571
00:40:52,695 --> 00:40:54,655
Come on, let's do this!

572
00:40:58,615 --> 00:40:59,855
That's it!

573
00:41:07,215 --> 00:41:08,535
Nice night, eh?

574
00:41:08,935 --> 00:41:11,535
Jesus Christ.

575
00:41:11,695 --> 00:41:13,455
That's Lonnie Washington's girl.

576
00:41:13,815 --> 00:41:15,335
Hell of a fighter.

577
00:41:15,535 --> 00:41:17,495
11-0.

578
00:41:17,655 --> 00:41:19,575
Your left. Keep your left up.

579
00:41:24,135 --> 00:41:26,135
Lonnie's got a lot of good fighters.

580
00:41:26,295 --> 00:41:29,295
He's got Joey Adagio,
lightweight champ?

581
00:41:29,495 --> 00:41:30,895
Yeah.

582
00:41:31,255 --> 00:41:33,015
Your left, damn it.

583
00:41:33,895 --> 00:41:38,375
Wouldn't have been my choice for
her first fight, but Sally's a good manager.

584
00:41:38,535 --> 00:41:41,135
-He must think she can take her.
-Jesus H.

585
00:41:41,335 --> 00:41:43,855
Your left. Keep your left up.

586
00:41:44,255 --> 00:41:47,135
You think she can hear you
from back here?

587
00:41:53,895 --> 00:41:57,495
Of course, if Maggie loses,
it wouldn't mean anything to Sally.

588
00:41:57,655 --> 00:41:59,575
Might even help him.

589
00:41:59,735 --> 00:42:01,575
Lonnie's girl gets another win...

590
00:42:01,735 --> 00:42:06,095
...Lonnie might let Sally's lightweight
fight Joey Adagio for the title.

591
00:42:06,375 --> 00:42:08,615
Sally's trying to set a fight with Adagio?

592
00:42:08,775 --> 00:42:10,135
Hey, what do I know?

593
00:42:10,295 --> 00:42:12,935
I just come because I enjoy the fights.

594
00:42:13,095 --> 00:42:15,535
Mother of God.

595
00:42:16,375 --> 00:42:17,815
Okay, break.

596
00:42:17,975 --> 00:42:20,255
Hey. Come here, come here.

597
00:42:20,415 --> 00:42:21,775
Hey. Get over here.

598
00:42:21,935 --> 00:42:24,655
You're dropping your left hand.
Quit dropping your left hand.

599
00:42:24,815 --> 00:42:27,415
Hey, Frankie,
you mind if I talk to my fighter?

600
00:42:27,575 --> 00:42:30,855
You're doing a hell of a job.
Is this the way you advise your lightweight?

601
00:42:31,335 --> 00:42:32,855
Dunn.

602
00:42:33,015 --> 00:42:35,415
-What are you doing?
-I'm talking. What are you doing?

603
00:42:35,575 --> 00:42:37,415
-Is this your fighter?
-It's my fighter.

604
00:42:38,695 --> 00:42:40,815
It ain't fitting real well, Sally.

605
00:42:41,015 --> 00:42:44,015
Fine, you take her.
She can't fight worth a shit anyway.

606
00:42:44,175 --> 00:42:48,375
-Somebody tell me what's going on.
-I was late. Sally was just subbing for me.

607
00:42:48,535 --> 00:42:50,895
You telling me this is your fighter?

608
00:42:53,015 --> 00:42:55,255
Yeah, this is my fighter.

609
00:42:55,415 --> 00:42:57,055
Then you got 10 seconds.

610
00:42:57,335 --> 00:43:00,375
I keep holding my left up,
then I throw a punch and it keeps dropping.

611
00:43:00,535 --> 00:43:02,535
-Well, let it drop.
-That'd be a lot easier.

612
00:43:02,695 --> 00:43:03,815
She thinks she knows you.

613
00:43:03,975 --> 00:43:06,855
Every time you drop it,
she comes right over the top.

614
00:43:07,055 --> 00:43:10,135
So you just wait for her, see?
That's all she's thinking about.

615
00:43:10,295 --> 00:43:13,175
-When she cocks that right hand-- You hear?
-I hear you, boss.

616
00:43:13,335 --> 00:43:16,215
When she does, step to the side
and come with a good-night hook.

617
00:43:16,375 --> 00:43:17,655
-Got one?
-Got it right here.

618
00:43:17,935 --> 00:43:20,495
-Okay.
-Fight, or I'm calling it.

619
00:43:20,655 --> 00:43:23,495
<i>-Go give it to her.
-The body knows what fighters don't.</i>

620
00:43:23,695 --> 00:43:24,855
<i>How to protect itself.</i>

621
00:43:25,495 --> 00:43:27,695
<i>A neck can only twist so far.</i>

622
00:43:27,895 --> 00:43:30,935
<i>Twist it just a hair more,
and the body says:</i>

623
00:43:31,095 --> 00:43:35,095
<i>"Hey, I'll take it from here because you
obviously don't know what you're doing. "</i>

624
00:43:35,255 --> 00:43:37,015
Neutral corner.

625
00:43:38,455 --> 00:43:40,215
-See the way she did that?
-Yeah.

626
00:43:40,375 --> 00:43:43,215
Sugar Ray would do that.
Girl's got sugar.

627
00:43:43,415 --> 00:43:48,815
<i>"Lie down, now, rest, and we'll talk
about this when you regain your senses. "</i>

628
00:43:48,975 --> 00:43:51,095
<i>It's called the knockout mechanism.</i>

629
00:43:51,255 --> 00:43:54,815
Don't get all carried away, now.
You did good.

630
00:43:54,975 --> 00:43:56,855
Thanks, boss.

631
00:43:57,215 --> 00:43:59,455
You.... You forgot the rule.

632
00:43:59,615 --> 00:44:01,935
-Now, what is the rule?
-Keep my left up?

633
00:44:02,135 --> 00:44:04,975
It's to protect yourself at all times.

634
00:44:05,495 --> 00:44:07,015
Now, what is the rule?

635
00:44:07,175 --> 00:44:10,375
-Protect myself at all times.
-Good, good.

636
00:44:10,535 --> 00:44:12,655
You gave me away.
How was that protecting me?

637
00:44:14,215 --> 00:44:15,375
It wasn't.

638
00:44:16,415 --> 00:44:17,895
It's okay.

639
00:44:18,615 --> 00:44:22,255
-I'll work on my left, boss.
-Drink your water.

640
00:44:23,335 --> 00:44:24,975
Other than that, how'd I do?

641
00:44:25,375 --> 00:44:28,135
Fine. You did fine.

642
00:44:29,055 --> 00:44:30,535
You gonna leave me again?

643
00:44:32,615 --> 00:44:34,215
Never.

644
00:44:34,375 --> 00:44:38,575
That place you work, do they have
homemade lemon meringue pie there?

645
00:44:39,095 --> 00:44:41,615
-Sure.
-Not the kind with the canned-filling crap?

646
00:44:41,775 --> 00:44:45,295
Oh, big can, yay size.
Says "homemade" on the label.

647
00:44:47,695 --> 00:44:50,575
-I want you to take the weekend off.
-It's only Thursday.

648
00:44:51,775 --> 00:44:55,255
-You gonna argue with me?
-Know better than to do that, boss.

649
00:44:55,855 --> 00:44:57,575
Well, good.

650
00:44:57,735 --> 00:45:00,295
<i>All fighters are pigheaded
some way or other.</i>

651
00:45:00,735 --> 00:45:04,015
<i>Some part of them always thinks
they know better than you about something.</i>

652
00:45:04,175 --> 00:45:08,255
Can you spare a few minutes
for the Immaculate Conception?

653
00:45:09,815 --> 00:45:13,495
<i>Truth is, even if they're wrong...</i>

654
00:45:13,655 --> 00:45:16,535
<i>...even if that one thing
is gonna be the ruin of them...</i>

655
00:45:16,695 --> 00:45:21,335
<i>...if you can beat that last bit out of them,
then they ain't fighters at all.</i>

656
00:45:21,495 --> 00:45:24,655
-Thought I said I'd see you Monday.
-You sure did, boss.

657
00:45:25,255 --> 00:45:26,455
That was last night.

658
00:45:26,615 --> 00:45:29,295
You said not to argue with you.

659
00:45:40,255 --> 00:45:42,855
Damn woman won't do a thing I tell her.

660
00:45:43,015 --> 00:45:44,895
You want my advice?

661
00:45:45,055 --> 00:45:46,455
What?

662
00:45:47,375 --> 00:45:48,775
Where are your shoes?

663
00:45:50,095 --> 00:45:52,015
I'm airing out my feet.

664
00:45:53,695 --> 00:45:55,495
You got big holes in your socks.

665
00:45:56,495 --> 00:45:58,375
Oh, they're not that big.

666
00:46:00,095 --> 00:46:02,255
Didn't I give you money
for some new ones?

667
00:46:03,855 --> 00:46:05,455
These are my sleeping socks.

668
00:46:06,775 --> 00:46:09,335
My feet like a little air at night.

669
00:46:09,895 --> 00:46:12,055
How come you're wearing them
in the daytime, then?

670
00:46:12,215 --> 00:46:15,095
Because my daytime socks
got too many holes in them.

671
00:46:17,295 --> 00:46:22,615
Well, if I give you some more money,
you buy some new socks.

672
00:46:22,935 --> 00:46:24,495
Please?

673
00:46:26,775 --> 00:46:30,455
Well, I'd be tempted,
but I couldn't say for sure.

674
00:46:30,615 --> 00:46:32,495
Might find its way to the track.

675
00:46:48,335 --> 00:46:51,415
It's over. It's over.

676
00:47:05,655 --> 00:47:08,215
<i>Didn't take Maggie long
to hit her stride.</i>

677
00:47:19,215 --> 00:47:20,575
I got the breathing thing down.

678
00:47:20,735 --> 00:47:24,135
No, you ain't breathing because you're
knocking them out in the first round.

679
00:47:24,335 --> 00:47:27,695
-Thought that was the point.
-The point is to get good.

680
00:47:28,335 --> 00:47:30,815
Can't get good if you keep
knocking them out first round.

681
00:47:30,975 --> 00:47:33,095
How am I gonna get you fights?

682
00:47:34,775 --> 00:47:37,015
Nobody wants to see
their fighter embarrassed, now.

683
00:47:37,175 --> 00:47:39,695
Why am I still doing
four-rounders, boss?

684
00:47:40,215 --> 00:47:42,375
Because you haven't got the lungs
for six rounds.

685
00:47:42,535 --> 00:47:45,615
I do if I keep knocking them out
in the first round.

686
00:47:49,375 --> 00:47:52,495
<i>Frankie made her fight
one more four-rounder...</i>

687
00:47:52,655 --> 00:47:54,735
<i>...just to let her know who was boss.</i>

688
00:47:58,615 --> 00:48:01,495
Three, four, five...

689
00:48:01,655 --> 00:48:03,695
...six, seven....

690
00:48:03,895 --> 00:48:05,415
Sorry, boss.

691
00:48:05,575 --> 00:48:07,535
<i>Maggie left no doubt about it.</i>

692
00:48:16,095 --> 00:48:19,215
All right, let's do it.

693
00:48:20,295 --> 00:48:24,135
<i>Her first six-rounder
didn't go quite as smooth.</i>

694
00:48:38,295 --> 00:48:40,015
Get up!

695
00:48:40,535 --> 00:48:41,775
To your corner.

696
00:48:41,975 --> 00:48:44,975
-Three, four, five...
-Get up.

697
00:48:45,175 --> 00:48:47,295
-...six, seven...
-Get up.

698
00:48:47,455 --> 00:48:50,375
-...eight, nine, ten. It's over.
-You can do this.

699
00:48:51,615 --> 00:48:55,895
<i>Maggie didn't knock her out
till the end of the first round.</i>

700
00:48:56,055 --> 00:49:00,015
<i>After that, no manager wanted
to put his fighter in with Maggie.</i>

701
00:49:03,895 --> 00:49:06,855
<i>Frankie had to go into his pocket
to get her decent fights...</i>

702
00:49:07,015 --> 00:49:10,855
<i>...sweetening the purse
by paying managers on the side.</i>

703
00:49:22,415 --> 00:49:24,775
<i>That only worked for so long.</i>

704
00:49:24,935 --> 00:49:27,935
<i>Then Frankie did something
he hated doing.</i>

705
00:49:28,095 --> 00:49:29,095
<i>He took a chance.</i>

706
00:49:31,735 --> 00:49:33,455
Box.

707
00:49:37,615 --> 00:49:39,975
<i>He moved her up in class.</i>

708
00:49:40,175 --> 00:49:42,895
<i>That could've been a mistake.</i>

709
00:49:55,255 --> 00:49:56,615
Watch the right!

710
00:49:58,895 --> 00:50:00,975
Watch it. Watch it.

711
00:50:07,615 --> 00:50:11,335
Break, break. Step back. Break. Time.

712
00:50:19,575 --> 00:50:21,935
Damn, damn, damn.

713
00:50:24,295 --> 00:50:25,695
Give us two seconds, will you?

714
00:50:25,855 --> 00:50:27,535
-Okay.
-Just two seconds.

715
00:50:28,295 --> 00:50:30,415
-Your nose is broke.
-Oh, damn.

716
00:50:30,615 --> 00:50:32,295
-Fix it.
-I can't, I can't.

717
00:50:32,455 --> 00:50:34,855
-You can fix it.
-I can't. I've gotta call it.

718
00:50:35,055 --> 00:50:36,855
I've seen what you can do. Fix it.

719
00:50:37,215 --> 00:50:39,935
I can snap it back into place,
but I can't stop the bleeding.

720
00:50:40,095 --> 00:50:41,575
The ring doctor's gonna call it.

721
00:50:41,735 --> 00:50:44,855
Please, Frankie, if you
can stop the blood, I can beat her.

722
00:50:46,255 --> 00:50:48,055
Bite down on this.

723
00:51:05,495 --> 00:51:06,895
-Inhale.
-What?

724
00:51:07,095 --> 00:51:08,455
-Inhale.
-What?

725
00:51:08,855 --> 00:51:10,495
Breathe in.

726
00:51:21,295 --> 00:51:23,895
-Okay, huh?
-Yeah, it's okay.

727
00:51:24,135 --> 00:51:27,095
All right, you got 20 seconds
before this turns into a geyser...

728
00:51:27,255 --> 00:51:29,295
...and it's gonna spray
all over the front row.

729
00:51:29,495 --> 00:51:31,575
Twenty seconds, that's all you've got.

730
00:51:31,735 --> 00:51:33,415
Now get going.

731
00:51:45,615 --> 00:51:47,375
Go to your corner.

732
00:51:48,495 --> 00:51:51,175
Three, four, five...

733
00:51:51,335 --> 00:51:54,895
-Come on, breathe. Breathe.
-...six, seven, eight...

734
00:51:55,055 --> 00:51:57,055
...nine, ten.

735
00:52:00,335 --> 00:52:01,735
<i>Mo cuishle.</i>

736
00:52:07,095 --> 00:52:08,735
-All right!
-Yeah!

737
00:52:10,535 --> 00:52:11,855
Right.

738
00:52:15,935 --> 00:52:17,615
What you reading?

739
00:52:18,495 --> 00:52:19,695
What's she saying?

740
00:52:20,255 --> 00:52:22,415
Wants to know what you're reading.

741
00:52:22,695 --> 00:52:25,415
It's Yeats. Keep your head back.

742
00:52:26,295 --> 00:52:28,175
Why don't you talk
a little Yeats to her.

743
00:52:28,335 --> 00:52:30,855
Show her what a treat that is.

744
00:52:31,415 --> 00:52:33,295
When the hell they gonna get to her?

745
00:52:33,455 --> 00:52:35,615
I'm okay, Frankie.

746
00:52:36,335 --> 00:52:39,175
-What'd you learn tonight?
-Always protect myself.

747
00:52:39,335 --> 00:52:42,295
-What's the rule?
-Always protect myself.

748
00:52:42,455 --> 00:52:44,255
-Margaret Fitzgerald?
-Here.

749
00:52:48,615 --> 00:52:50,495
I'll be right here.

750
00:53:01,975 --> 00:53:04,335
-How you doing?
-Me?

751
00:53:04,495 --> 00:53:06,375
-Yeah, you.
-I'm not the one who's hurt.

752
00:53:11,055 --> 00:53:12,775
Broken nose don't hurt that much.

753
00:53:13,495 --> 00:53:15,695
Why are you telling me that?

754
00:53:17,775 --> 00:53:19,055
No reason.

755
00:53:19,255 --> 00:53:23,255
<i>But some wounds are too deep
or too close to the bone.</i>

756
00:53:23,575 --> 00:53:27,895
<i>And no matter how hard you work at it,
you just can't stop the bleeding.</i>

757
00:53:28,055 --> 00:53:31,295
-Did you write your daughter?
-Every week.

758
00:53:32,775 --> 00:53:35,655
I've no idea why you come to church.

759
00:54:05,575 --> 00:54:10,095
<i>After her 12th straight knockout,
Frankie got a couple of real good offers.</i>

760
00:54:12,535 --> 00:54:15,055
<i>The first was to fight
Billie "The Blue Bear" Osterman...</i>

761
00:54:15,215 --> 00:54:17,455
<i>...for the WBA welterweight title.</i>

762
00:54:19,335 --> 00:54:21,055
Billie "The Blue Bear."

763
00:54:21,215 --> 00:54:24,215
<i>Billie was a former prostitute
out of East Berlin.</i>

764
00:54:24,375 --> 00:54:28,415
<i>Had a reputation for being
the dirtiest fighter in the ranks.</i>

765
00:54:46,095 --> 00:54:47,455
<i>Didn't seem to matter to her...</i>

766
00:54:47,615 --> 00:54:50,135
<i>...that something like that
could kill a person.</i>

767
00:54:51,015 --> 00:54:53,135
<i>And the crowds loved her.</i>

768
00:54:55,935 --> 00:54:58,775
<i>He turned it down
without even telling her.</i>

769
00:54:58,935 --> 00:55:01,135
<i>The next was to fight
the British champ...</i>

770
00:55:01,295 --> 00:55:04,455
<i>-...a Jamaican girl Billie just beat.
-Hello?</i>

771
00:55:05,215 --> 00:55:07,135
Not interested.

772
00:55:09,855 --> 00:55:12,295
<i>He turned that down too.</i>

773
00:55:14,415 --> 00:55:16,615
That's a lot of money, boss.

774
00:55:16,775 --> 00:55:20,095
Yeah, you're making money.
What are you still working here for?

775
00:55:20,255 --> 00:55:21,895
It's a title match, right?

776
00:55:22,055 --> 00:55:24,935
Are you British?
It's a title you can't take away.

777
00:55:25,095 --> 00:55:28,295
She's got nothing to lose,
you got nothing to win.

778
00:55:29,055 --> 00:55:31,495
Might still be a good fight.

779
00:55:31,695 --> 00:55:35,055
Yeah, I just-- I just brought you up
to welterweight.

780
00:55:35,215 --> 00:55:38,535
Too good to fight these contenders,
you'd rather fight some bullshit champ?

781
00:55:38,735 --> 00:55:41,575
Didn't notice I was fighting
any contenders.

782
00:55:42,375 --> 00:55:45,415
Well, you can get yourself
another manager any time you want.

783
00:55:46,455 --> 00:55:49,255
In fact, if you'd learn
to protect your face a little better...

784
00:55:49,415 --> 00:55:51,815
...I wouldn't have
to turn down this money.

785
00:55:55,055 --> 00:55:58,455
My face is out there so much it's a miracle
I haven't been knocked out yet.

786
00:56:27,150 --> 00:56:28,910
No, you can't work here
anymore tonight.

787
00:56:29,910 --> 00:56:31,630
I made us a reservation.

788
00:56:32,910 --> 00:56:35,310
You might wanna shower.

789
00:56:55,830 --> 00:56:57,870
Here you go.

790
00:56:58,070 --> 00:56:59,830
Here you go.

791
00:57:00,310 --> 00:57:01,950
What's this?

792
00:57:02,110 --> 00:57:05,270
Well, it ain't no big secret
what you're wishing for.

793
00:57:05,790 --> 00:57:07,190
Go on and blow.

794
00:57:11,910 --> 00:57:13,590
Thank you.

795
00:57:17,510 --> 00:57:19,910
Thirty-three ain't so old.

796
00:57:20,630 --> 00:57:23,350
I was still fighting at 39.

797
00:57:24,590 --> 00:57:26,990
Fought for 23 years.

798
00:57:30,590 --> 00:57:32,190
How's it going, Scrap?

799
00:57:32,350 --> 00:57:33,950
Doing good, Mickey.

800
00:57:34,990 --> 00:57:36,710
Doing good.

801
00:57:38,070 --> 00:57:40,470
-What'll you have?
-Coffee.

802
00:57:45,750 --> 00:57:47,950
You two not speaking?

803
00:57:48,350 --> 00:57:50,510
Don't hardly know him.

804
00:57:55,230 --> 00:57:59,270
I met Frankie right after
my 37th birthday.

805
00:58:00,270 --> 00:58:02,710
He was picking up cut work.

806
00:58:03,670 --> 00:58:07,190
He used to patch me up
when I thought it was impossible.

807
00:58:08,470 --> 00:58:10,390
Good man to have in your corner.

808
00:58:11,310 --> 00:58:13,150
Yes, he is.

809
00:58:14,670 --> 00:58:17,750
He stayed with me
through my last fight in San Berdu.

810
00:58:18,510 --> 00:58:21,790
My manager was off
getting drunk somewhere...

811
00:58:22,350 --> 00:58:25,670
...and it was just Frankie and me.

812
00:58:27,470 --> 00:58:30,190
I was taking a hellacious beating.

813
00:58:31,550 --> 00:58:34,750
Everybody's got a particular number
of fights in him.

814
00:58:35,430 --> 00:58:38,230
Nobody tells you what that number is.

815
00:58:39,150 --> 00:58:41,710
Mine was 109.

816
00:58:42,270 --> 00:58:44,470
I just didn't want to admit it.

817
00:58:46,150 --> 00:58:48,390
Fourth round, this...

818
00:58:49,070 --> 00:58:50,430
...cut opens up.

819
00:58:50,870 --> 00:58:53,590
Blood starts pouring into my eye.

820
00:58:55,390 --> 00:58:59,190
They should've stopped the fight, but,
hell, I was a black man in San Berdu.

821
00:58:59,390 --> 00:59:01,470
Blood was what I was there for.

822
00:59:02,310 --> 00:59:05,710
Round after round, I kept getting
Frankie to patch me up.

823
00:59:06,270 --> 00:59:08,190
He's talking about
throwing in the towel...

824
00:59:08,350 --> 00:59:11,550
...but he ain't my manager,
he can't throw in nothing.

825
00:59:12,550 --> 00:59:14,710
Round after round...

826
00:59:14,870 --> 00:59:17,110
...he's arguing with me.

827
00:59:18,430 --> 00:59:22,350
And I'm almost laughing because, hell,
it's getting more to him than to me.

828
00:59:23,230 --> 00:59:25,630
I go 15 rounds...

829
00:59:25,790 --> 00:59:27,950
...Iose by decision.

830
00:59:28,590 --> 00:59:30,870
Next morning, I lose the eye.

831
00:59:33,270 --> 00:59:36,630
In 23 years, he's never said
a thing about it.

832
00:59:37,550 --> 00:59:41,430
Doesn't have to. I can see it
in his face every time he looks at me.

833
00:59:42,230 --> 00:59:43,990
Somehow...

834
00:59:44,910 --> 00:59:47,470
...Frankie thinks he should've
stopped that fight...

835
00:59:48,310 --> 00:59:50,550
...should've saved my eye.

836
00:59:52,670 --> 00:59:56,590
Spends his life wishing he could
take back that 109th fight.

837
00:59:57,430 --> 01:00:00,230
I wanted to go to 110.

838
01:00:00,790 --> 01:00:02,710
Thing is...

839
01:00:03,350 --> 01:00:05,110
...if you wanna get to the title...

840
01:00:06,350 --> 01:00:08,910
...maybe he's not the one
to take you there.

841
01:00:13,910 --> 01:00:15,950
You tell Mr. Mack we'd be here tonight?

842
01:00:19,030 --> 01:00:21,150
You go on, eat your cupcake.

843
01:00:21,310 --> 01:00:23,950
No, I got it.

844
01:00:29,270 --> 01:00:30,590
<i>It's the rule.</i>

845
01:00:30,750 --> 01:00:33,070
<i>Always protect yourself.</i>

846
01:00:33,590 --> 01:00:36,310
<i>People never take their own advice.</i>

847
01:00:36,470 --> 01:00:41,310
<i>If she was gonna leave Frankie,
better she did it to him then.</i>

848
01:00:45,470 --> 01:00:47,350
Mr. Mickey Mack?

849
01:00:47,510 --> 01:00:49,750
I'm Maggie Fitzgerald.

850
01:00:50,070 --> 01:00:55,550
I hear you're a real good manager,
doing good things for Big Willie.

851
01:00:55,990 --> 01:00:58,910
But I thought you should know
I ain't never leaving Mr. Dunn...

852
01:00:59,830 --> 01:01:02,670
...so you don't need to make any more
excuses to bump into me.

853
01:01:04,630 --> 01:01:06,950
Sorry for interrupting your dinner.

854
01:01:10,550 --> 01:01:14,510
<i>Maggie always did like
taking them out in the first round.</i>

855
01:01:46,350 --> 01:01:50,070
<i>The letters always came back
marked the same way:</i>

856
01:01:50,230 --> 01:01:52,310
<i>"Return to sender. "</i>

857
01:02:20,630 --> 01:02:23,070
I'll make you some coffee.

858
01:02:24,950 --> 01:02:26,550
What are you doing with your money?

859
01:02:27,150 --> 01:02:29,150
-Saving it.
-Good girl.

860
01:02:30,910 --> 01:02:34,190
You know, you save enough of it,
you ought to get yourself a little house.

861
01:02:34,350 --> 01:02:35,630
Cash, no mortgage.

862
01:02:35,790 --> 01:02:38,230
Gonna be a while before I can do that.

863
01:02:41,230 --> 01:02:44,310
Yeah, well, it might be a stretch...

864
01:02:44,470 --> 01:02:46,990
...but you gotta get yourself
a place of your own.

865
01:02:47,190 --> 01:02:50,270
Go around wasting it on things
that don't matter and what do you got?

866
01:02:50,670 --> 01:02:52,070
You understand?

867
01:02:52,310 --> 01:02:55,990
Pretty soon, you wait long enough,
you got nothing.

868
01:02:56,150 --> 01:02:58,030
Okay, soon as I get the money.

869
01:02:58,230 --> 01:03:02,110
I made a lot of mistakes in my life. I'm just
trying to keep you from doing the same.

870
01:03:02,550 --> 01:03:04,110
I know, boss.

871
01:03:05,390 --> 01:03:07,750
-I'm not gonna live forever.
-What is it?

872
01:03:07,910 --> 01:03:10,470
It's a tape on that girl in England
you're gonna fight.

873
01:03:10,710 --> 01:03:13,830
If you're gonna go for the title,
we got some moves to-- Hey.

874
01:03:13,990 --> 01:03:16,550
Hey, get the hell down.
You know how old I am?

875
01:03:16,710 --> 01:03:19,230
-Thank you, boss. Thank you so much.
-Yeah.

876
01:03:19,390 --> 01:03:23,670
You're welcome, darling. Here, just--
Here, let me put this in the machine.

877
01:03:23,830 --> 01:03:25,750
What machine?

878
01:03:26,350 --> 01:03:27,830
Don't have a TV, huh?

879
01:03:27,990 --> 01:03:29,710
No.

880
01:03:30,350 --> 01:03:32,030
Yeah!

881
01:03:32,510 --> 01:03:35,110
All right. Okay.

882
01:03:40,950 --> 01:03:43,310
-Ten minutes, love.
-Thank you.

883
01:03:43,630 --> 01:03:44,990
Man says he loves me.

884
01:03:45,150 --> 01:03:47,150
He's probably not
the first one to say that.

885
01:03:47,350 --> 01:03:49,470
First since my daddy.

886
01:03:50,070 --> 01:03:51,670
I win, you think he'll propose?

887
01:03:52,030 --> 01:03:54,070
You win, I'll propose.

888
01:03:57,750 --> 01:03:59,590
Look, I got you a gift here.

889
01:04:04,590 --> 01:04:06,350
I think they gave you somebody else's.

890
01:04:06,510 --> 01:04:08,390
No, no, this is it.

891
01:04:09,390 --> 01:04:10,790
What's it mean?

892
01:04:10,950 --> 01:04:14,630
I don't know.
Just something in Gaelic.

893
01:04:15,510 --> 01:04:19,070
-It's beautiful.
-Yeah, I thought so.

894
01:04:19,230 --> 01:04:20,990
-Yeah.
-Real silk thread.

895
01:04:24,470 --> 01:04:28,630
From the United States
of America, the challenger...

896
01:04:28,790 --> 01:04:31,990
...Maggie Fitzgerald.

897
01:04:33,670 --> 01:04:35,670
<i>Mo cuishle.
Did you see what was on her robe?</i>

898
01:04:35,830 --> 01:04:38,030
<i>-Mo cuishle. Mo cuishle.
-Mo cuishle.</i>

899
01:04:42,070 --> 01:04:43,830
<i>She wasn't the main attraction.</i>

900
01:04:43,990 --> 01:04:47,510
<i>She was on the undercard
of a middleweight title fight.</i>

901
01:04:47,870 --> 01:04:49,790
<i>But ask someone who was there...</i>

902
01:04:49,950 --> 01:04:52,830
<i>...they couldn't tell you who else
fought that night.</i>

903
01:04:58,710 --> 01:05:00,310
Box.

904
01:05:20,030 --> 01:05:21,470
<i>-Come on!
-Mo cuishle!</i>

905
01:05:22,150 --> 01:05:26,150
<i>Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!</i>

906
01:05:27,310 --> 01:05:28,870
<i>Mo cuishle!</i>

907
01:05:30,110 --> 01:05:31,150
<i>Mo cuishle!</i>

908
01:05:32,950 --> 01:05:35,830
<i>Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!</i>

909
01:05:44,270 --> 01:05:45,910
She's tough.

910
01:05:47,550 --> 01:05:49,910
I can't get inside.
I can't get close enough to hit her.

911
01:05:50,070 --> 01:05:52,430
-You know why that is?
-Why?

912
01:05:52,830 --> 01:05:54,710
She's a better fighter than you are.

913
01:05:54,870 --> 01:05:58,790
She's younger, she's stronger,
and she's more experienced. Now...

914
01:05:58,950 --> 01:06:01,070
...what are you gonna do about it?

915
01:06:08,790 --> 01:06:10,470
Get in there.

916
01:06:11,190 --> 01:06:12,670
Box.

917
01:06:25,750 --> 01:06:30,350
Three, four, five, six...

918
01:06:30,510 --> 01:06:35,470
...seven, eight, nine, ten.

919
01:06:36,150 --> 01:06:39,550
<i>Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!</i>

920
01:06:46,390 --> 01:06:49,590
<i>-Mo cuishle!
-Mo cuishle!</i>

921
01:06:56,470 --> 01:06:58,550
I could ask someone, you know?

922
01:06:59,110 --> 01:07:00,390
Good.

923
01:07:00,550 --> 01:07:02,510
You find out, you let me know.

924
01:07:09,430 --> 01:07:12,110
<i>Whatever it meant, the name stuck.</i>

925
01:07:12,270 --> 01:07:16,630
<i>Maggie fought in Edinburgh and Paris,
Brussels and Amsterdam.</i>

926
01:07:16,790 --> 01:07:19,510
<i>It was always mo cuishle.</i>

927
01:07:19,750 --> 01:07:21,990
<i>Seems there are
Irish people everywhere...</i>

928
01:07:22,150 --> 01:07:24,390
<i>...or people who wanna be.</i>

929
01:07:24,790 --> 01:07:27,150
<i>By the time they came back
to the States...</i>

930
01:07:27,990 --> 01:07:30,950
<i>...Maggie was in a whole new league.</i>

931
01:07:47,350 --> 01:07:51,630
<i>Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle! Mo cuishle!</i>

932
01:08:01,110 --> 01:08:04,110
<i>After that they got another offer
to fight for the title.</i>

933
01:08:06,390 --> 01:08:08,190
What's the split?

934
01:08:08,750 --> 01:08:11,070
-Sixty-forty.
-Good.

935
01:08:11,230 --> 01:08:15,030
We'll take 60 and you take 40,
being as that Maggie's the draw.

936
01:08:15,510 --> 01:08:16,870
That little girl?

937
01:08:17,270 --> 01:08:20,470
You think I'm wrong, really?
You think people are saying...

938
01:08:20,630 --> 01:08:24,270
...that they wanna see some scabby Kraut
beat up on little Miss What's-Her-Name?

939
01:08:24,430 --> 01:08:27,350
You find someone who says that,
and we'll take the 40.

940
01:08:34,590 --> 01:08:36,230
There you go.

941
01:08:39,030 --> 01:08:42,670
They're at 60-40,
but they'll come up to 50-50.

942
01:08:43,390 --> 01:08:45,070
How's that girl doing?

