01:30:56,510 --> 01:30:58,110
Where's Frankie?

1189
01:31:00,150 --> 01:31:01,510
Well, he's....

1190
01:31:01,670 --> 01:31:03,950
He's out there talking to the doctors.

1191
01:31:04,150 --> 01:31:07,110
Probably telling them how to do their job.

1192
01:31:09,270 --> 01:31:13,430
They're telling him
I'm a C1 and C2 complete.

1193
01:31:16,550 --> 01:31:21,070
Means that my spinal cord's so broke
they'll never be able to fix it.

1194
01:31:24,550 --> 01:31:27,990
Gonna be frozen like this
the rest of my life.

1195
01:31:32,790 --> 01:31:36,510
I asked them to tell him.
I don't know how he's gonna take it.

1196
01:31:44,590 --> 01:31:46,510
Did you see the fight?

1197
01:31:48,990 --> 01:31:50,630
Of course I did.

1198
01:31:51,630 --> 01:31:53,470
You had her cold, Maggie.

1199
01:31:55,030 --> 01:31:57,870
I shouldn't have dropped my hands.

1200
01:32:01,590 --> 01:32:03,670
I shouldn't have turned.

1201
01:32:10,390 --> 01:32:12,150
Always protect myself.

1202
01:32:12,310 --> 01:32:15,310
How many times he tell me that?

1203
01:32:16,470 --> 01:32:17,830
Yeah...

1204
01:32:18,830 --> 01:32:20,910
...he does like to repeat himself.

1205
01:32:24,550 --> 01:32:27,750
Will you tell him I'm real sorry?

1206
01:32:31,630 --> 01:32:33,030
No.

1207
01:32:33,710 --> 01:32:35,870
I won't do no such thing, Maggie.

1208
01:32:55,190 --> 01:32:56,710
Damnedest thing.

1209
01:33:00,390 --> 01:33:02,070
So, what's the plan?

1210
01:33:02,910 --> 01:33:06,070
I know you got one,
so you might as well tell me what it is.

1211
01:33:06,230 --> 01:33:07,950
It's your fault.

1212
01:33:08,510 --> 01:33:11,390
Yeah, it's your fault
she's lying in there like that.

1213
01:33:11,550 --> 01:33:13,430
You kept after me until I trained her.

1214
01:33:13,910 --> 01:33:16,710
I knew I shouldn't have done it,
her being a girl and all.

1215
01:33:17,710 --> 01:33:20,070
Everything kept telling me not to.

1216
01:33:20,230 --> 01:33:21,910
Everything but you.

1217
01:33:31,950 --> 01:33:33,550
I'm gonna get you out of here.

1218
01:33:33,710 --> 01:33:35,590
These doctors around here
don't know squat.

1219
01:33:35,750 --> 01:33:38,590
Otherwise, why would they be
living out here in the desert?

1220
01:33:39,430 --> 01:33:41,590
As soon as you're able to be moved...

1221
01:33:41,910 --> 01:33:45,390
...we'll find some place where
they've actually studied medicine.

1222
01:33:48,150 --> 01:33:50,030
You just rest there, I'II....

1223
01:33:51,750 --> 01:33:53,270
I'm on it.

1224
01:34:01,990 --> 01:34:04,270
<i>Frankie must have called
every hospital in America...</i>

1225
01:34:04,470 --> 01:34:07,150
<i>...looking for somebody
who'd tell him they could fix her.</i>

1226
01:34:07,310 --> 01:34:11,190
<i>He came close twice,
till they checked her over...</i>

1227
01:34:11,510 --> 01:34:13,430
<i>...said there was nothing to be done.</i>

1228
01:34:13,910 --> 01:34:16,990
<i>Took two months till she was
stable enough to move.</i>

1229
01:34:22,070 --> 01:34:24,470
They got nurses for that, you know.

1230
01:34:25,870 --> 01:34:28,030
Yeah, but they're amateurs.

1231
01:34:39,670 --> 01:34:43,790
<i>She developed skin ulcers
because she couldn't change positions.</i>

1232
01:34:54,390 --> 01:34:55,910
Thank you.

1233
01:35:05,470 --> 01:35:08,710
<i>They made the six-hour trip
by ambulance.</i>

1234
01:35:19,630 --> 01:35:22,350
Fly there, drive back.

1235
01:35:28,470 --> 01:35:31,750
<i>The rehab center Frankie found
was a nice place.</i>

1236
01:35:32,230 --> 01:35:33,950
<i>They took good care of Maggie.</i>

1237
01:35:34,110 --> 01:35:36,110
<i>She wouldn't have complained
if they hadn't.</i>

1238
01:35:37,350 --> 01:35:41,150
<i>Took several hours every day
to get her ready for the wheelchair.</i>

1239
01:35:46,150 --> 01:35:48,350
One, two, three, up.

1240
01:35:50,670 --> 01:35:52,910
<i>Since she couldn't breathe on her own...</i>

1241
01:35:53,070 --> 01:35:55,590
<i>...her respirators were always on.</i>

1242
01:35:56,790 --> 01:36:00,430
<i>Oxygen was pumped into her
24 hours a day.</i>

1243
01:36:25,550 --> 01:36:28,790
<i>Maggie's mama called to say
they were all coming for a visit.</i>

1244
01:36:28,950 --> 01:36:32,430
<i>She waited by the window
every day for the next two weeks.</i>

1245
01:36:33,390 --> 01:36:34,630
Sure.

1246
01:36:34,790 --> 01:36:37,270
<i>Frankie finally tracked them down.</i>

1247
01:36:37,430 --> 01:36:41,270
<i>Learned they'd checked into their hotel
six days earlier.</i>

1248
01:36:41,430 --> 01:36:44,670
<i>Kept leaving messages
which were never returned.</i>

1249
01:36:48,590 --> 01:36:51,150
You don't have to hang around all day.

1250
01:36:54,830 --> 01:36:57,670
I like it here. I don't mind.

1251
01:36:58,390 --> 01:37:02,190
In fact, if you weren't here,
I'd come here anyway to read my books.

1252
01:37:04,950 --> 01:37:07,790
Mama will be here soon
to share some of the burden.

1253
01:37:08,150 --> 01:37:09,870
Well, it's no burden.

1254
01:37:10,790 --> 01:37:12,150
Here.

1255
01:37:14,110 --> 01:37:15,350
Read this.

1256
01:37:24,150 --> 01:37:26,150
Okay, okay, that's enough.

1257
01:37:26,590 --> 01:37:27,990
That's terrible.

1258
01:37:30,390 --> 01:37:33,270
Anyway, I'll tell you in English
what you were saying.

1259
01:37:36,070 --> 01:37:37,470
It says:

1260
01:37:37,630 --> 01:37:41,030
<i>I will arise and go now
And go to Innisfree</i>

1261
01:37:41,230 --> 01:37:45,550
<i>And a small cabin build there
Of clay and wattles made</i>

1262
01:37:46,430 --> 01:37:50,670
<i>And I shall have some peace there
For peace comes dropping slow</i>

1263
01:37:51,230 --> 01:37:55,750
<i>Dropping from the veils of the morning
To where the cricket sings.</i>

1264
01:37:58,030 --> 01:37:59,350
Not bad, huh?

1265
01:38:03,670 --> 01:38:05,750
You gonna build a cabin, boss?

1266
01:38:06,390 --> 01:38:08,150
-Me?
-Yeah.

1267
01:38:10,430 --> 01:38:13,070
You know, when you quit all this.

1268
01:38:14,950 --> 01:38:16,510
You mean boxing?

1269
01:38:17,070 --> 01:38:19,590
No, I'll never quit.

1270
01:38:20,550 --> 01:38:22,950
I like the stink too much, I guess.

1271
01:38:28,590 --> 01:38:30,990
You think?
Because I could see you there real easy...

1272
01:38:31,190 --> 01:38:33,430
...with your books and lemon pie.

1273
01:38:35,510 --> 01:38:38,310
How about you?
Would you like to go live in a cabin?

1274
01:38:40,270 --> 01:38:42,430
I could learn how to bake.

1275
01:38:46,230 --> 01:38:47,670
Well, then, I'II....

1276
01:38:47,830 --> 01:38:49,910
Maybe I'll start looking then.

1277
01:39:10,750 --> 01:39:12,190
Yeah.

1278
01:39:14,870 --> 01:39:17,150
-Go ahead.
-All right. Okay, sounds good.

1279
01:39:20,910 --> 01:39:23,190
Hi, I'm Frankie Dunn.
I met you back out in Missouri.

1280
01:39:23,350 --> 01:39:24,590
Where's my little girl?

1281
01:39:24,790 --> 01:39:27,470
Don't you think you ought to go back
to the hotel and change?

1282
01:39:27,670 --> 01:39:30,310
She doesn't know you've been here
a week visiting Woody and Mickey.

1283
01:39:30,470 --> 01:39:33,790
We got business with my sister.
Why don't you just tell us where she is.

1284
01:39:33,950 --> 01:39:36,590
Oh, you must be J.D.
And you must be the business guy?

1285
01:39:36,750 --> 01:39:38,110
There's some rides you missed.

1286
01:39:38,270 --> 01:39:40,830
Why don't you go back.
I'll tell her you couldn't make it.

1287
01:39:40,990 --> 01:39:43,150
I drove all the way here
to take care of my child.

1288
01:39:43,350 --> 01:39:45,390
And you're suggesting
I'm not a good mother?

1289
01:39:45,590 --> 01:39:47,150
Mary M. can't go nowhere.

1290
01:39:47,310 --> 01:39:50,190
If we could've taken her to Disneyland,
we would've.

1291
01:39:51,670 --> 01:39:52,790
Margaret Fitzgerald?

1292
01:39:53,270 --> 01:39:54,870
Right down here, 301.

1293
01:39:55,190 --> 01:39:56,790
-Come on, Mama.
-Let's go.

1294
01:40:03,030 --> 01:40:05,030
And I saw myself breathing.

1295
01:40:05,230 --> 01:40:06,990
Like, my body was going up and down.

1296
01:40:07,190 --> 01:40:09,870
I thought,
"Why didn't somebody tell me?"

1297
01:40:13,230 --> 01:40:15,950
Your hair needs washing.
It's kind of greasy.

1298
01:40:29,470 --> 01:40:30,790
It's just a....

1299
01:40:31,750 --> 01:40:33,750
It's just some kind of legal thing.

1300
01:40:33,950 --> 01:40:35,190
What is it?

1301
01:40:35,350 --> 01:40:37,350
How we all doing here?

1302
01:40:37,510 --> 01:40:39,910
Sorry, darling,
but we ain't got a lot of time.

1303
01:40:40,110 --> 01:40:44,110
Mr. Johnson's charging us a lot of money
to be here to make sure this is done proper.

1304
01:40:44,270 --> 01:40:46,790
Why don't you just leave that.
I'll read it to her later.

1305
01:40:46,950 --> 01:40:48,430
Hey, old man...

1306
01:40:48,630 --> 01:40:50,030
...you part of our family?

1307
01:40:50,910 --> 01:40:52,510
Stay the hell out of this.

1308
01:40:54,070 --> 01:40:55,710
Read it to me, Mama.

1309
01:40:55,870 --> 01:40:59,270
Well, it's just something legal
to protect your money.

1310
01:41:00,030 --> 01:41:01,510
Mama, you don't have to worry.

1311
01:41:02,310 --> 01:41:05,590
The boxing commission's
paying for all this, everything.

1312
01:41:05,950 --> 01:41:07,990
But what if they don't, Mary M?

1313
01:41:08,150 --> 01:41:10,870
Mr. Johnson says
they can take my house.

1314
01:41:11,030 --> 01:41:14,070
If you assign your assets to your mother,
no one can touch them.

1315
01:41:14,230 --> 01:41:15,990
No doctors, no funeral expenses.

1316
01:41:16,790 --> 01:41:19,630
-Nothing.
-Yeah, look, why don't you just leave it.

1317
01:41:19,830 --> 01:41:23,510
-Then I'll just read it to her later on--
-With respect, this ain't your business.

1318
01:41:24,950 --> 01:41:27,270
All right. I'll be out in the hall.

1319
01:41:33,270 --> 01:41:35,510
You been a good daughter, Mary M.

1320
01:41:37,070 --> 01:41:38,750
You sign that paper...

1321
01:41:39,150 --> 01:41:41,150
...it'll take care of your family...

1322
01:41:41,430 --> 01:41:43,590
...the way your daddy
would've wanted you to.

1323
01:41:48,150 --> 01:41:50,070
How do you make your mark?

1324
01:41:52,510 --> 01:41:53,670
Can you hold a pen?

1325
01:41:53,830 --> 01:41:56,110
She gotta do it with her teeth, Mama.

1326
01:41:56,270 --> 01:41:58,230
You gotta put it in her mouth.

1327
01:41:59,590 --> 01:42:01,230
Here you go, honey.

1328
01:42:04,230 --> 01:42:06,190
Did you see the fight, Mama?

1329
01:42:06,470 --> 01:42:08,550
Honey, you know how I feel about that.

1330
01:42:09,990 --> 01:42:11,550
I did pretty good.

1331
01:42:11,710 --> 01:42:13,510
You lost, Mary M.

1332
01:42:14,390 --> 01:42:17,950
Ain't your fault, the way I heard it,
but you lost.

1333
01:42:19,510 --> 01:42:22,150
Don't wanna lose the rest
of what you got left.

1334
01:42:22,550 --> 01:42:24,070
There you go.

1335
01:42:32,990 --> 01:42:34,830
What happened to you?

1336
01:42:35,150 --> 01:42:36,750
Well, what's that supposed to mean?

1337
01:42:38,550 --> 01:42:41,830
Mama, you take Mardell and J.D.
and get home.

1338
01:42:43,590 --> 01:42:46,790
Before I tell that lawyer that you were
so worried about your welfare...

1339
01:42:46,950 --> 01:42:50,030
...you never signed those house papers
like you were supposed to.

1340
01:42:52,750 --> 01:42:55,070
So any time I feel like it,
I can sell that house...

1341
01:42:55,230 --> 01:42:58,350
...from under your fat, lazy,
hillbilly asses.

1342
01:43:00,350 --> 01:43:03,470
And if you ever come back,
that's exactly what I'll do.

1343
01:43:43,110 --> 01:43:47,070
Well, maybe someone ought
to count to 10.

1344
01:44:00,070 --> 01:44:02,110
Don't smell real pretty, does it, doc?

1345
01:44:04,950 --> 01:44:06,470
We might have to lose it, Maggie.

1346
01:45:20,310 --> 01:45:23,030
They took my leg, boss.

1347
01:45:27,710 --> 01:45:30,070
It's gonna be all right, you hear?

1348
01:45:30,870 --> 01:45:34,150
I always hear your voice, boss.

1349
01:46:04,590 --> 01:46:06,070
You need anything?

1350
01:46:09,710 --> 01:46:12,230
<i>I need to know what "mo cuishle" means.</i>

1351
01:46:13,910 --> 01:46:15,630
But you didn't win.

1352
01:46:16,190 --> 01:46:18,030
I don't have to tell you.

1353
01:46:21,590 --> 01:46:24,070
You're the meanest man I ever met.

1354
01:46:24,230 --> 01:46:26,430
No wonder no one loves you.

1355
01:46:29,870 --> 01:46:32,150
You remind me of my daddy.

1356
01:46:34,750 --> 01:46:36,630
Well, he must have been...

1357
01:46:37,110 --> 01:46:40,270
...a very intelligent, handsome man.

1358
01:46:43,950 --> 01:46:46,990
You ain't gonna make me talk
no more Yeats, are you?

1359
01:46:48,830 --> 01:46:50,190
No, I was...

1360
01:46:51,630 --> 01:46:54,430
...Iooking at this catalog
from City College.

1361
01:46:56,630 --> 01:46:58,870
I thought I'd get you a wheelchair...

1362
01:46:59,310 --> 01:47:02,590
...maybe the kind that operates
by blowing through a straw.

1363
01:47:03,350 --> 01:47:06,190
I thought maybe you'd like
to go back to school.

1364
01:47:11,070 --> 01:47:13,390
I got a favor to ask you, boss.

1365
01:47:15,510 --> 01:47:17,190
Sure.

1366
01:47:18,510 --> 01:47:20,390
Anything you want.

1367
01:47:22,070 --> 01:47:24,910
Remember what my daddy did for Axel?

1368
01:47:37,230 --> 01:47:39,630
Don't even think about that.

1369
01:47:43,350 --> 01:47:45,670
I can't be like this, Frankie.

1370
01:47:48,750 --> 01:47:50,470
Not after what I done.

1371
01:47:50,630 --> 01:47:52,550
I seen the world.

1372
01:47:55,470 --> 01:47:57,590
People chanted my name.

1373
01:47:58,550 --> 01:47:59,670
Well...

1374
01:48:01,550 --> 01:48:04,870
...not my name,
some damn name you gave me.

1375
01:48:07,790 --> 01:48:10,150
But they were chanting for me.

1376
01:48:13,550 --> 01:48:15,790
I was in magazines.

1377
01:48:19,430 --> 01:48:22,070
You think I ever dreamed that'd happen?

1378
01:48:26,310 --> 01:48:29,830
I was born at 2 pounds,
1 and a half ounces.

1379
01:48:33,110 --> 01:48:36,550
Daddy used to tell me
I fought to get into this world...

1380
01:48:39,790 --> 01:48:42,030
...and I'd fight my way out.

1381
01:48:46,790 --> 01:48:49,590
That's all I wanna do, Frankie.

1382
01:48:51,670 --> 01:48:54,030
I just don't wanna fight you to do it.

1383
01:48:56,870 --> 01:48:58,190
I got what I needed.

1384
01:49:02,030 --> 01:49:04,390
I got it all.

1385
01:49:07,790 --> 01:49:10,710
Don't let them keep
taking it away from me.

1386
01:49:15,590 --> 01:49:20,350
Don't let me lie here till I can't hear
those people chanting no more.

1387
01:49:25,110 --> 01:49:27,310
I can't.

1388
01:49:27,990 --> 01:49:29,990
Please.

1389
01:49:31,950 --> 01:49:34,310
Please, don't ask me.

1390
01:49:36,350 --> 01:49:38,350
I'm asking.

1391
01:49:41,790 --> 01:49:43,630
I can't.

1392
01:50:25,710 --> 01:50:27,590
Hello?

1393
01:50:32,590 --> 01:50:34,750
<i>In the middle of the night...</i>

1394
01:50:34,910 --> 01:50:37,790
<i>...Maggie had found her own solution.</i>

1395
01:50:38,350 --> 01:50:40,430
<i>She had bit her tongue.</i>

1396
01:50:47,230 --> 01:50:49,950
Stop. Stop.

1397
01:50:53,270 --> 01:50:55,790
Look at me. Look at me.

1398
01:51:09,550 --> 01:51:13,150
<i>Nearly bled to death
before they stitched her up.</i>

1399
01:51:13,590 --> 01:51:17,750
<i>She came around and ripped them out
before Frankie even got there.</i>

1400
01:51:18,030 --> 01:51:20,110
<i>They stitched her up again...</i>

1401
01:51:20,310 --> 01:51:23,350
<i>...padded the tongue
so she couldn't bite.</i>

1402
01:51:40,910 --> 01:51:43,150
You can't do it, you know that.

1403
01:51:44,910 --> 01:51:46,830
I do, Father.

1404
01:51:47,750 --> 01:51:49,630
But you don't know how thick she is...

1405
01:51:49,790 --> 01:51:52,230
...how hard it was to train her.

1406
01:51:52,630 --> 01:51:56,350
Other fighters would do
exactly what you'd say to them...

1407
01:51:56,510 --> 01:52:01,750
...and she'd ask, why this and why that,
and then do it her own way anyway.

1408
01:52:02,430 --> 01:52:04,590
How she fought for the title, I....

1409
01:52:04,750 --> 01:52:06,190
It wasn't by anything....

1410
01:52:06,390 --> 01:52:09,270
Well, it wasn't by listening to me.

1411
01:52:17,950 --> 01:52:20,150
But now she wants to die...

1412
01:52:20,310 --> 01:52:22,470
...and I just wanna keep her with me.

1413
01:52:26,630 --> 01:52:30,670
And I swear to God, Father, it's....

1414
01:52:31,150 --> 01:52:33,870
It's committing a sin by doing it.

1415
01:52:34,030 --> 01:52:37,310
By keeping her alive, I'm killing her.

1416
01:52:37,710 --> 01:52:40,590
Do you know what I mean?
How do I get around that?

1417
01:52:41,870 --> 01:52:44,590
You don't. You step aside, Frankie.

1418
01:52:44,750 --> 01:52:46,630
You leave her with God.

1419
01:52:47,270 --> 01:52:50,670
She's not asking for God's help.
She's asking for mine.

1420
01:52:50,830 --> 01:52:54,630
Frankie, I've seen you at Mass
almost every day for 23 years.

1421
01:52:54,830 --> 01:52:56,750
The only person comes
to church that much...

1422
01:52:56,910 --> 01:52:58,510
...is the kind who can't
forgive himself for something.

1423
01:52:58,670 --> 01:53:00,950
Whatever sins you're carrying...

1424
01:53:01,430 --> 01:53:03,790
...they're nothing compared to this.

1425
01:53:04,150 --> 01:53:08,150
Forget about God or heaven and hell.

1426
01:53:08,310 --> 01:53:11,270
If you do this thing, you'll be lost.

1427
01:53:14,590 --> 01:53:16,750
Somewhere so deep...

1428
01:53:18,510 --> 01:53:20,830
...you'll never find yourself again.

1429
01:53:26,750 --> 01:53:29,070
I think I did it already.

1430
01:53:50,070 --> 01:53:53,270
We're keeping her sedated
so she won't try that again.

1431
01:54:55,790 --> 01:54:58,350
I went to see Maggie this morning.

1432
01:55:00,030 --> 01:55:01,950
You must have been somewhere else.

1433
01:55:03,070 --> 01:55:04,870
Yeah.

1434
01:55:08,550 --> 01:55:10,550
You got a fight I don't know about?

1435
01:55:15,750 --> 01:55:17,910
It wasn't your fault.

1436
01:55:18,350 --> 01:55:20,390
I was wrong to say that.

1437
01:55:20,630 --> 01:55:22,510
You're damn right.

1438
01:55:23,830 --> 01:55:25,110
I found you a fighter...

1439
01:55:25,270 --> 01:55:28,670
...and you made her
the best fighter she could be.

1440
01:55:31,150 --> 01:55:32,550
I killed her.

1441
01:55:32,710 --> 01:55:34,510
Don't say that.

1442
01:55:34,870 --> 01:55:37,310
Maggie walked through that door
with nothing but guts.

1443
01:55:37,470 --> 01:55:40,550
No chance in the world of being
what she needed to be.

1444
01:55:40,710 --> 01:55:43,950
A year and a half later, she's fighting
for the championship of the world.

1445
01:55:44,110 --> 01:55:45,310
You did that.

1446
01:55:47,470 --> 01:55:49,870
People die every day, Frankie.

1447
01:55:50,030 --> 01:55:51,830
Mopping floors, washing dishes.

1448
01:55:52,150 --> 01:55:54,030
And you know what
their last thought is?

1449
01:55:54,190 --> 01:55:56,550
"I never got my shot."

1450
01:55:57,030 --> 01:55:59,230
Because of you, Maggie got her shot.

1451
01:56:00,430 --> 01:56:03,950
If she dies today, you know what
her last thought will be?

1452
01:56:04,790 --> 01:56:07,070
"I think I did all right."

1453
01:56:14,350 --> 01:56:16,830
I know I could rest with that.

1454
01:56:19,390 --> 01:56:20,390
Yeah.

1455
01:56:20,950 --> 01:56:22,710
Yeah.

1456
01:56:33,310 --> 01:56:34,950
Yeah.

1457
01:57:11,630 --> 01:57:12,990
I'm gonna get a cup of coffee.

1458
01:57:13,150 --> 01:57:14,590
Yeah.

1459
01:57:40,430 --> 01:57:41,990
All right.

1460
01:57:45,990 --> 01:57:48,350
I'm gonna disconnect your air machine...

1461
01:57:49,190 --> 01:57:51,350
...then you're gonna go to sleep.

1462
01:57:55,870 --> 01:57:58,510
Then I'll give you a shot, and you'II...

1463
01:57:59,550 --> 01:58:01,070
...stay asleep.

1464
01:58:06,190 --> 01:58:07,910
<i>Mo cuishle...</i>

1465
01:58:09,390 --> 01:58:12,830
...means "my darling, my blood."

1466
01:59:18,150 --> 01:59:20,830
<i>He gave her a single shot.</i>

1467
01:59:21,190 --> 01:59:25,230
<i>It was enough adrenaline
to do the job a few times over.</i>

1468
01:59:25,550 --> 01:59:28,310
<i>He didn't want her
going through this again.</i>

1469
02:00:16,110 --> 02:00:17,750
<i>Then he walked out.</i>

1470
02:00:18,350 --> 02:00:21,510
<i>I don't think he had anything left.</i>

1471
02:00:39,310 --> 02:00:41,430
<i>I went back to the gym.</i>

1472
02:00:41,710 --> 02:00:45,230
<i>Waited, figuring he'd turn up
sooner or later.</i>

1473
02:01:04,070 --> 02:01:07,350
<i>And that's when a ghost
came through the door.</i>

1474
02:01:09,790 --> 02:01:12,710
I got to thinking what you said,
Mr. Scrap.

1475
02:01:13,750 --> 02:01:15,350
What was that, Danger?

1476
02:01:16,910 --> 02:01:19,390
Anybody can lose one fight.

1477
02:01:20,590 --> 02:01:22,350
That's the truth.

1478
02:01:23,150 --> 02:01:25,590
Go on, put your gloves on.
You missed a lot of training.

1479
02:01:27,470 --> 02:01:29,870
Will do, Mr. Scrap. Sure thing.

1480
02:01:47,910 --> 02:01:50,910
<i>Frankie never came back at all.</i>

1481
02:02:05,070 --> 02:02:09,070
<i>Frankie didn't leave a note,
and nobody knew where he went.</i>

1482
02:02:09,390 --> 02:02:11,830
<i>I'd hoped he'd gone to find you...</i>

1483
02:02:11,990 --> 02:02:14,870
<i>...and ask you one more time
to forgive him.</i>

1484
02:02:15,030 --> 02:02:18,350
<i>But maybe he didn't have
anything left in his heart.</i>

1485
02:02:18,510 --> 02:02:21,710
<i>I just hope he found someplace
where he could find a little peace.</i>

1486
02:02:22,190 --> 02:02:25,150
<i>A place set in the cedars and oak trees.</i>

1487
02:02:25,510 --> 02:02:28,590
<i>Somewhere between
nowhere and goodbye.</i>

1488
02:02:28,750 --> 02:02:32,150
<i>But that's probably wishful thinking.</i>

1489
02:02:32,630 --> 02:02:34,550
<i>No matter where he is...</i>

1490
02:02:35,070 --> 02:02:39,630
<i>...I thought you should know what kind
of man your father really was.</i>

1491
02:06:59,590 --> 02:07:01,510
[ENGLISH]